    elif n == 1: 
        return 1

    else : 
        # recur on subproblem of length 2 
        return fibonacci(2*n-1)+fibonacci((2*n)-2); 

Here, f(n) would represent the running time of the program, which depends on the size of n (the input parameter). The expression f(n)*constant + o(f(n)), where constant is some small number, expresses the fact that the running time grows roughly proportional to n, but there will be a slowdown as n gets larger due to the overhead caused by recursions.

